  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (MRL 3)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 3. Twelve of thirteen factors are assessed and meet required levels; one factor (Use error) is recorded as not-assessed on the basis that the assessment team considered it inapplicable to an internally-operated CFD workflow — however the correct encoding for that determination would be factorStatus 'not-applicable', not 'not-assessed'. At MRL 3 this omission materially weakens credibility.",
