    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen credibility factors assessed and meeting or exceeding required levels at MRL 3. Validation results demonstrate NIH predictions within experimental uncertainty across all COU operating points. The Use error factor was recorded as not-assessed on the basis of an informal applicability judgment by the assessment team; this determination was not formally encoded as 'not-applicable' and no documentary evidence was provided to support the exemption. The decision record accepts the package pending formal resolution of the Use error factor status, which the team considers low-priority given the controlled internal analysis environment. This reasoning, while plausible, does not satisfy the MRL 3 requirement for a complete credibility factor assessment.",
